Vulnerability	Risk	Solution
Hardcoded Wi-Fi SSID and Password	Credentials can be stolen if the code is shared.	Store credentials in config.h and exclude it using .gitignore.
Using HTTP instead of HTTPS	Data can be intercepted or modified by attackers.	Use HTTPS with SSL/TLS encryption.
Public MQTT Broker without Authentication	Anyone can publish or subscribe to messages.	Use MQTT username/password authentication and TLS.
No Validation of Incoming Commands	Attackers can send malicious commands to the device.	Validate all received commands before executing them.
No Data Encryption	Sensitive data is transmitted in plain text.	Encrypt communication using TLS/SSL.
